{
  "name": "Effortless Paralysis",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Genjutsu.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You create a visual image of your own description that grabs and restrains a creature you can see within range. The target must succeed a Wisdom Saving throw. This jutsu has no effect on undead, constructs, plants, or Demons.</p><p>Success: Affected creature is able to resist this genjutsu's effects.</p><p>Failure: Affected creature becomes paralyzed for the duration. A paralyzed creature remakes their save at the end of each of its turns or when it takes damage, ending this jutsu's effect on it, on a success.</p><p>Critical Failure: Same effect as failure, but affected creature also only makes its saves when it takes damage.</p>",
